The <strong><code>onload</code></strong> property of the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/GlobalEventHandlers" title="The GlobalEventHandlers mixin describes the event handlers common to several interfaces like HTMLElement, Document, or Window."><code>GlobalEventHandlers</code></a> mixin is an <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventHandler" title="REDIRECT DOM event handlers"><code>EventHandler</code></a> that processes <code><a href="/en-US/docs/Web/Events/load" title="/en-US/docs/Web/Events/load">load</a></code> events on a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window" title="The Window interface represents a window containing a DOM document; the document property points to the DOM document loaded in that window."><code>Window</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLHttpRequest" title="Use XMLHttpRequest (XHR) objects to interact with servers. You can retrieve data from a URL without having to do a full page refresh. This enables a Web page to update just part of a page without disrupting what the user is doing."><code>XMLHttpRequest</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/img" title="The HTML &lt;img&gt; element embeds an image into the document. It is a replaced element."><code>&lt;img&gt;</code></a> element, etc.